The paper focuses on evaluating the perceived quality of generative models through human perception, specifically in the context of image generation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques and models, indicating that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also draws on psychophysics research in perception, which suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and cost of the evaluation method, indicating that it may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
